<span id="xiii.ii.i.i-p86"></span> The district, called Mareotis from a
neighbouring lake, lay in the territory and diocese of Alexandria, to
the south-west. It consisted of various large villages, with handsome
Churches, and resident Priests, and of hamlets which had none; of the
latter was “Irene of Secontarurus)” (infr. §85.) where Ischyras lived.

